User intent: Create a commit. Info: {prompt}
Focus on generating a highly descriptive and professional commit message based on the actual code changes (diff) and user intent. YOU MUST FOLLOW the Conventional Commits specification. The format should be `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`.
Allowed types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore, revert.
Determine the `<scope>` based on the files modified (e.g., `core`, `config`, `cli`). Provide the exact bash git command(s), including `git add` if necessary. Critically: use the Recent Commits to match the formatting, casing, and style of previous commits in this project.

